Those "troll science" comics from 2011 are sort of perennial because if you went back to like 17th century Sweden the concept of "what if trolls had their own unusual and paradoxical laws of physics" would still make sense. You can imagine all of it as folklore about real trolls.

Like a 14th century text claiming that mountain trolls walk on each other's feet up towards the sky or jump down a valley on a bench and then jump off the bench before crashing down. It sounds like stuff real life trolls also would do. Not a big expert though don't have any here.

Opened a half-empty bottle of orange juice I had forgotten in my gym bag and it popped, gas had built up below the cap, pretty sure it had started to ferment. If you forget a bottle of intra-workout grape juice in your sweaty duffle bag, you will end up w/ miraculous gymcel wine.

I bet it has happened before. Gym bros forget their intra-workout carbs sugary grape juice bottles in their gym bags all summer carrying them around the heat and storing them in cool lockers to find them full of wine once autumn come and to drink it. It becomes a ceremony. Kafka.

Sorta like Dr. Peat said try carrying lettuce in one of your pockets and carrots in the other and walk around in those pants all day on a hot summer day and see what happens to one and to the other. But in the secret third pocket you carry grapes and make the wine of the gymcels.
